<C>__{michael}
<D>__{tom is right.}
<C>__{connie}
<D>__{kids, why don't you go outside for a while?}
<A>__{the children don't move; connie realizes they will only listen to michael.}
<C>__{connie}
<D>__{i want to talk to you, michael.}
<C>__{michael}
<D>__{the children can stay.}
<C>__{connie}
<D>__{i hated you for so long, michael; for so many years. i think i did things to myself, to hurt myself, so that you would know and you would be hurt too. but i understand you now; i think i do. you were being strong for all of us, like papa was. and i forgive you, and want to be close to you now. can't you forgive fredo; he's so sweet, and helpless without you.}
<A>__{slowly, michael puts his hand on her hair, and touches her gently.}
<C>__{connie}
<D>__{you need me, michael. i want to be with you now.}
